Class ServerConstants

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.stephanlajaunie.projects.messaging.service.server.ServerConstants

  • public class ServerConstants
extends java.lang.Object
    Encapsulates many of the common server-side logs, messages, prompts, etc that may be used.
    Author:
    slajaunie

      Logs that the server received an Object that is not an instance of Protocol

      Logs that the server received a command/command string that was not recognized/ did not conform to the expected protocol
      static java.lang.String ERROR_INDEX_OUT_OF_BOUNDS
      Logs that the specified message number (e.g., in a FORWARD or DELETE command) does not exist in the given account's MessageStore

      Logs that the Server via the AccountManager was unable to locate the requested user account

      static java.lang.String LOG_AUTH_VERIFYING
      Logs that an AUTH command was sent, and the AccountManager will verify the information sent
      static java.lang.String LOG_COMMAND_RECEIVED

      static java.lang.String LOG_COMMAND_WRITTEN
      Logs that a command was sent back to the client

      Logs that the server socket has accepted a connection from a client

      static java.lang.String LOG_CONFIRM_HELLO
      Logs that the server has received a HELLO command from a client
      static java.lang.String LOG_CONFIRM_LISTENING

      static java.lang.String LOG_CONFIRM_SHUTDOWN
      Logs that the server socket is shutting down (due to an error)
      static java.lang.String LOG_SEND_MESSAGES
      Logs that the Server is sending the contents of a MessageStore to the client, probably in response to a READ command
      static java.lang.String LOG_STORE_MSG_SUCCESS
      Logs that the Server was able to save the received message via the AccountManager in the requested account's MessageStore
